A user has a knowledge graph with 12,000 nodes across 8 domain partitions. They notice that synthesis cycles are producing many low-quality nodes that get rejected by quality gates, especially in cross-domain pairs. The similarity threshold is set to 0.5 (floor) and 0.92 (ceiling). What could cause this pattern, and what specific adjustments would you recommend to improve synthesis quality without reducing the discovery of novel cross-domain connections? Consider the trade-offs involved.